<http://identifiers.org/rgd/1306853>
        a       owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_5358  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: \"TRAF6-facilitated K63 ubiquitination was diminished in K558R (Fig. S3B) and PSD-95ΔNT (Fig. 3D) mutants. In vitro ubiquitination assays using purified proteins showed that TRAF6, in conjunction with Ubc13/Uev1A, effectively delivered the ubiquitin moieties to PSD-95, which did not occur when TRAF6, UbK63, Ubc13, Uev1A, or PSD-95 was omitted from the reaction mix (Fig. 3E).\"\n\n\"Knocking down TRAF6 prevented the AP5-elicited increase of PSD-95 ubiquitination (Fig. 7G), supporting the notion that TRAF6 mediates constitutive K63 ubiquitination of PSD-95.\"\n\n\"The activity-dependent assembly/disassembly of K63-polyUb chains may involve dynamic regulation of the E2-E3-substrate-DUB multiprotein complex we have identified in the PSD. The Ubc13/Uev1A dimer remains the only known K63-selective E2 that, together with the RING-domain family E3 ligase TRAF6, catalyzes the assembly of K63-polyUb chains on substrates. Our results suggest that the Ubc13/Uev1A-TRAF6 complex binds the PSD-95 NT and delivers ubiquitin moieties to cognate lysine sites.\". Experimental description: M&M: \"high-density (1 × 106) hippocampal neurons were prepared from E18 rat embryos\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-13" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5358" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

